<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter" src="https://images-us.bookshop.org/ingram/9781635422924.jpg?height=500&amp;v=v2" alt="Wild: Poems - Okri, Ben" width="200" height="300" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Ben Okri, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781635422924" class="external" target="_blank">Wild: Poems</a><br />
</em>(Other Press)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;[Okriâ€™s] writing takes on the great riddles of existenceâ€”freedom and consciousness, truth and illusion, suffering and transcendenceâ€”spinning them into shimmering, allegorical textsâ€¦at a time of deep reckoning and crisis&#8230;his work feel[s] all the more prescient.&#8221;<br />
