<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;A posthumously published work by a major (if unsung) Black novelist reminds readers of his imaginative brio, verbal ingenuity, and abrasive wit&#8230;.All you can do is marvel at Kelley&#8217;s arresting collage-like portrait of the artist as an intellectual nomad, clinging to the core of what makes him humanâ€”and humane. There&#8217;s cleverness and craft in abundance here. Also, wisdom and even warmth.&#8221;<br />
